The paper deals with the problem of identifying infected individuals within a large population using group testing. This involves designing efficient algorithms and determining the minimum number of tests required to identify the status of all individuals. These topics are closely related to information theory (cs.IT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), statistical inference (cs.SI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
